{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"enunciable-delirious-loon","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe plan-review `[rebar:<C>]` citation-escape lets a plan cite a symbol a prerequisite ticket\nwill create; the E4/G1G2/E6 finders are instructed to \"retrieve C via the `show_ticket(C)` tool\"\nand credit the citation only if C's plan establishes the functionality\n(`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_E4.md:16`, `plan_review_G1G2.md:10`). The agentic finder's\n`show_ticket` tool is `rebar.llm.pai_tools.rebar_tools`'s inner `show_ticket`\n(`src/rebar/llm/pai_tools.py:204`), which forwards its argument verbatim to\n`_reads.show_ticket`.\n\n**Defect:** the citation token is literally `[rebar:<id>]`, so the finder passes the token content\n**`rebar:<id>` — including the `rebar:` scheme** — to the tool. rebar's id resolver does not\nrecognize the `rebar:` prefix, so `rebar show 'rebar:<id>'` exits \"Ticket not found,\" the finder\ncannot confirm the prerequisite, and the citation-escape **fails closed on a spurious\n\"cited prerequisite does not exist\"** BLOCK. Runtime-proven by an instrumented review: the finder\ncalled `show_ticket('rebar:8153-…')` and `show_ticket('rebar:fc72-…')` (both → \"not found\") while\nthe bare-id call `show_ticket('41e2-…')` returned OK. Because the LLM only *sometimes* strips the\nprefix itself, the failure is intermittent — which is why some citing plans pass and others block.\nThis breaks the documented citation mechanism (`docs/writing-a-passing-plan.md` \"Citing a\nprerequisite's symbol\").\n\n## Approach\n\nNormalize the agent-supplied ticket ref at the tool boundary — the single site where a\n`rebar:`-scheme ref originates. Add `_normalize_ticket_ref()` to `pai_tools.py` that strips a\nleading `rebar:` (case-insensitive) plus any wrapping `[]`/whitespace, and call it in both\n`show_ticket` and `comment_ticket` before resolving. Stripping is unambiguous and safe: no ticket\nid (hex groups `[a-z0-9]{4}-…`) or alias (hyphenated words) contains a colon, so a leading\n`rebar:` is never part of a real id; the function is idempotent on a bare id.\n\n**Rejected alternative.** Fixing it in the reviewer prompts (tell the LLM to strip the scheme) —\nprobabilistic (LLM may still forget) versus a deterministic tool-boundary normalization. Rejected\nwidening `_reads.show_ticket` / the CLI id-resolver — the `rebar:` scheme only ever arrives from\nthe LLM citation-token path, so normalizing at that boundary keeps CLI/library id semantics\nuntouched.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/pai_tools.py` — add `_normalize_ticket_ref`; apply in `show_ticket` and\n  `comment_ticket`.\n- `tests/interfaces/store/test_scoped_ticket_tool.py` — add a RED-first case pinning that the tool\n  resolves a `rebar:<id>`-form ref.\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy path (the defect): `show_ticket(f\"rebar:{tid}\")` resolves to the same ticket as the bare\n  `tid` — returns the ticket JSON (title + id present), not `Error: … not found`. Fails RED against\n  the current tool; passes after the strip.\n- Parity: the existing `test_show_ticket_tool_reads` (bare id) and `test_comment_ticket_tool_comments`\n  still pass — a bare id is unchanged (idempotent normalization).\n\nTier: unit (interfaces/store) — builds a real store via the `rebar_repo` fixture, creates a ticket,\ninvokes the actual `rebar_tools` `show_ticket` function; no LLM.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The agentic `show_ticket` tool resolves a `rebar:<id>`-scheme ref to the same ticket as the\n      bare id; verified by\n      `rtk .venv/bin/pytest -q tests/interfaces/store/test_scoped_ticket_tool.py -k rebar_scheme_prefix`\n      (the new case passes).\n- [ ] Bare-id reads and comments are unchanged (parity); verified by\n      `rtk .venv/bin/pytest -q tests/interfaces/store/test_scoped_ticket_tool.py`\n      (the full file passes, including the pre-existing read/comment cases).","id":"a643-1c30-0bb0-46ee","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":["review-architecture","plan-review","citation"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Plan-review show_ticket tool rejects the rebar: citation-scheme prefix, breaking the [rebar:<C>] escape"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784693277791276001,"uuid":"05e4ae68-a14c-4f9b-af6b-b8412038aec3"}